<type>[optional scope][!]: <description>

[optional body: explain what changed and why]

Project-Source: <plan|milestone|task|prompt|manual>
Project-Plan: <.agents/plans/PLAN_*.md or omit>
Project-Milestone: <milestone name or omit>
Project-Task: <repo-task slug/title or omit>
Project-Prompt: <short direct-request summary or omit>
Co-authored-by: <agent-name> <agent-email>
Refs: <paths/issues/PRs or omit>
Validation: <command/result>

# Conventional Commits 1.0.0 shape:
#   <type>[optional scope][optional !]: <description>
#   [optional body]
#   [optional footer(s)]
#
# Repository types:
#   feat      new user-facing or API behavior
#   fix       bug fix
#   docs      documentation-only change
#   test      test, benchmark, or manual-regression harness change
#   refactor  internal code change with no behavior change
#   chore     repository maintenance
#   build     build, dependency, or tooling change
#   ci        CI or release automation change
#   perf      performance improvement
#   style     formatting-only change
#   revert    revert a previous commit
#
# Breaking changes are disallowed while ROADMAP.md says so.
# Use ! or a BREAKING CHANGE: footer only when the repo's breaking-change policy permits it.
#
# Project metadata footers:
#   Project-Source is required for AI-created commits.
#   Co-authored-by footer is required for AI-created commits.
#   Use plan for whole-plan or plan/spec-only commits.
#   Use milestone for one named plan milestone.
#   Use task for a repo-task starter.
#   Use prompt for a direct ad hoc user request.
#   Use manual only for human-authored commits outside the AI workflow.
#   Include only the Project-* footers that apply.
#   Validation is required for AI-created commits; say "not run" with a reason when needed.
#
# Examples:
#   feat(books): add publication-year search filter
#
#   Project-Source: prompt
#   Project-Prompt: add publication-year search filter
#   Co-authored-by: <agent-name> <agent-email>
#   Validation: ./build.ps1 build - green
#
#   fix(security): reject forged csrf headers
#   docs(plan): update manual regression workflow
#   test(manual-regression): add execution log example report
